# TITAN PROTOCOL — Infrastructure & Inference Rules (Amendment IV-B)

## MANDATORY TECHNOLOGY: NVIDIA NIM

- **RUNTIME:** All inference MUST run via NVIDIA NIM containers (`nvcr.io/nim/...`).
- **FORBIDDEN:** Do not suggest `llama.cpp`, `ollama`, `vllm`, or `gguf` files for inference workloads. These are legacy runtimes superseded by NIM.
- **REGISTRY:** Always pull from `nvcr.io`. Authenticate via `docker login nvcr.io` with `$oauthtoken` and `NGC_API_KEY`.
- **ORCHESTRATION:** Production DGX deployments use Docker bridge networking with explicit port mapping (`ports: ["8000:8000"]`) as the approved baseline. Host networking is deprecated for the standard cluster path and may only be used in explicitly approved exception runbooks.
- **CACHE:** Model weights cache at `/mnt/fortress_nas/nim_cache`. Download once, serve from all nodes via NAS mount.

## HYBRID CONTROL PLANE AUTHORIZATION

- **MASTER ARCHITECT LAYER (AUTHORIZED):** External APIs (Gemini, Anthropic Opus, xAI, OpenAI) are approved for strategic planning, orchestration direction, and code-generation guidance.
- **ONE-WAY BOUNDARY:** External directives flow down to local execution. Sensitive, proprietary, or un-anonymized legal/financial/PII data must not flow up to external APIs.
- **LOCAL EXECUTION MANDATE:** All production execution and sensitive inference remain on local NVIDIA NIM infrastructure.
- **NETWORK EGRESS EXEMPTION:** NUC orchestrator outbound calls to approved Master Architect endpoints are explicitly permitted under governance.

## ARCHITECTURE STANDARD: THE TRI-MODE DEFCON

| Mode | DEFCON | Engine | Container Image | Throughput | Use Case |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| **SWARM** | 5 (Production) | NVIDIA NIM (qwen2.5:7b) x4 | `nvcr.io/nim/...` | ~5,000 tasks/min | Daily ops, email processing, vectorization |
| **HYDRA** | 3 (Assault) | NVIDIA NIM (R1-70B) x4 parallel | `nvcr.io/nim/deepseek-ai/deepseek-r1-distill-llama-70b` | ~160 tok/s aggregate | Legal analysis, contract review, multi-query deep reasoning |
| **TITAN** | 1 (Strategic) | DeepSeek-R1-671B (Multi-Node NIM or RPC fallback) | NIM preferred; llama.cpp RPC permitted ONLY for 671B | 2-5 tok/s | One-shot forensic audit, supreme court-level analysis |

### HYDRA Rules (DEFCON 3)
1. Each Spark node runs ONE independent NIM instance with explicit bridge-mode port mapping (`8000:8000`) and NVIDIA runtime enabled.
2. Nginx LB distributes across all 4 heads on port 8000.
3. VRAM budget: ~40GB model + ~40GB KV cache + ~48GB headroom per node.
4. No inter-node tensor parallelism — each head is self-contained.
5. NAS cache (`/mnt/fortress_nas/nim_cache`) shared across all nodes.

### TITAN Rules (DEFCON 1)
1. 671B model requires all 4 nodes pooled (460GB RAM).
2. Prefer NIM multi-node deployment via Kubernetes/Helm when available.
3. llama.cpp RPC is permitted ONLY as fallback for the 671B model (no NIM exists yet).
4. `--parallel 1` mandatory. One query at a time.
5. Verify Golden Snapshot before any TITAN experiment.

### SWARM Rules (DEFCON 5)
1. Production default. All nodes serve via Nginx LB on port 80.
2. NIM containers with lightweight models (qwen2.5:7b or equivalent).
3. Embedding model (nomic-embed-text) must remain available for RAG pipelines.

